subSubSection.paragraph:
Median lobe of aedeagus (
Figs. 122–124
) in lateral view slender, strongly arcuate, with apical portion slightly curved dorsally and with very apex bent ventrally; in dorsal view widened behind the middle and evenly narrowed in apical third; ventral side slightly impressed; terminal lamella (
Fig. 122
) wide and long, longer than wide, narrowed posteriorly, concave on dorsal side and narrowly rounded at apex. Apical orifice in dorsal position, wide apically. Internal sac with a group of small spines on the left side behind the middle.

Female genitalia (
Figs. 125 & 126
): gonocoxite comparatively wide in ventral and lateral view, about 0.7 times as long as gonosubcoxite, with rather wide base.
